experiences.description:
JCDecaux is Australia and New Zealand’s most progressive Outdoor advertising company; leaders in the Street Furniture, Digital Billboard, Billboard, Transit, Rail and Airport advertising categories. 

I act as a strategic business partner to the executive team, providing high-level financial leadership, strategic insights and decision support to enable the achievement of commercial objectives. With oversight of all financial, accounting, compliance and systems activities and the ongoing development of leadership capabilities, I work closely with the CFO in external and internal finance matters, supporting presentations and stakeholder engagement initiatives. Key focus areas and achievements have included:

•	Improved collaboration between divisions through a business partnering structure, improving forecasting accuracy and provision of data and commercial decision support to the business;
•	Initiated, planned and delivered a company-wide business systems migration from JDE to Oracle;
•	Established standard financial reporting frameworks and developed improved risk management processes, streamlining operations, reducing costs and enhancing business risk maturity.

Applying financial skills and business acumen to provide advice and direction to a family business, I drove an agenda of business improvement, optimising revenue and profit performance through involvement across all aspects of the business. Interfacing with clients whilst holding an internal leadership role, I participated heavily in business development activities as well as the strengthening of back-office business systems and processes.

•	Responsible for business development and relationship building with clients across various sectors;
•	Realised business efficiencies and scalability through the development of systems and processes

Joining three weeks after the company was listed on the ASX, I was responsible for implementing financial management and turnaround strategies to lift business performance. Working in an environment under threat from the rise of digital media offerings and in a industry with competitive margins, the implementation of lean thinking was key to drive business profitability. Developing performance management tools, identifying redundancies, negotiating with suppliers and banks and providing oversight for payroll, tax, accounts payable, accounts receivable and divisional operations, I worked to improve productivity and profitability across all business functions.

•	Realised a significant reduction in operating costs across the organisation with the business returning to a profit-making enterprise through formulation and delivery of turnaround and lean process strategies;
•	Significantly improved productivity and accountability through the design of comprehensive, KPI-based performance evaluation processes.
